{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_36f90d33-711e-4f7f-9ab4-cbe6155a10e","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/nodemailer/nodemailer","query":"createTransport sendMail raw MIME messageId references inReplyTo SentMessageInfo envelope accepted rejected error codes EAUTH"},"toolCallId":"tool_36f90d33-711e-4f7f-9ab4-cbe6155a10e","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### sendMail\n\nSource: https://github.com/nodemailer/nodemailer/blob/master/_autodocs/api-reference/mailer.md\n\nSends an email using the configured transport. It can be used with callbacks or Promises.\n\n```APIDOC\n## sendMail\n\nSends an email using the configured transport.\n\n### Method\n\n`transporter.sendMail(messageData, callback)` or `await transporter.sendMail(messageData)`\n\n### Parameters\n\n#### Data Object\n- **data** (object) - Required - Message data object.\n- **callback** (function) - Optional - Callback function `(err, info)` or omit for Promise.\n\n### Message Data Object Properties\n\n- **from** (string | AddressObject) - Required - Sender address.\n- **to** (string | array) - Recipient(s).\n- **cc** (string | array) - Carbon copy recipient(s).\n- **bcc** (string | array) - Blind carbon copy recipient(s).\n- **sender** (string | AddressObject) - Sender for Resent-Sender header.\n- **replyTo** (string | AddressObject) - Reply-To address.\n- **subject** (string) - Email subject line.\n- **text** (string | Buffer | stream) - Plain text body.\n- **html** (string | Buffer | stream) - HTML body.\n- **amp** (string | Buffer | stream) - AMP for Email body.\n- **attachments** (array) - Array of attachment objects.\n- **alternatives** (array) - Alternative body formats.\n- **headers** (object) - Custom email headers.\n- **messageId** (string) - Message-ID header value.\n- **date** (Date) - Date header value.\n- **priority** ('high' | 'normal' | 'low') - Message priority.\n- **icalEvent** (object) - iCalendar event object.\n- **dkim** (object) - Per-message DKIM config.\n- **envelope** (object) - Explicit SMTP envelope.\n- **raw** (string | Buffer | stream) - Pre-formatted RFC822 message.\n\n### Attachment Object Properties\n\n- **filename** (string) - Attachment filename.\n- **content** (string | Buffer | stream) - File content.\n- **path** (string) - Path to file on disk.\n- **href** (string) - URL to file.\n- **contentType** (string) - MIME type.\n- **contentDisposition** ('attachment' | 'inline') - 'attachment' or 'inline'.\n- **contentTransferEncoding** (string) - Encoding type.\n- **contentId** (string) - Content-ID for inline images.\n- **cid** (string) - Alias for contentId.\n- **headers** (object) - Custom headers for this attachment.\n\n### Address Object Example\n\n```json\n{\n    \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n    \"address\": \"john@example.com\"\n}\n```\n\n### Response Type (SendResult Object)\n\n```json\n{\n    \"envelope\": {\n        \"from\": \"sender@example.com\",\n        \"to\": [\"recipient@example.com\"]\n    },\n    \"messageId\": \"<unique-id@example.com>\",\n    \"response\": \"Message accepted for delivery\"\n}\n```\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### SendResult\n\nSource: https://github.com/nodemailer/nodemailer/blob/master/_autodocs/types.md\n\nThe SendResult object is returned from `transporter.sendMail()` and contains information about the sent email, including message ID, server response, and transport-specific fields.\n\n```APIDOC\n## SendResult\n\nResult object returned from `transporter.sendMail()`.\n\n### Definition\n\n```javascript\n{\n    envelope: {\n        from: string,              // Sender address\n        to: array                  // Recipient addresses\n    },\n    messageId: string,             // Generated Message-ID (e.g., '<id@host>')\n    response: string,              // Server response (SMTP only)\n    \n    // Transport-specific fields may follow:\n    // Stream transport:\n    message: stream | Buffer,      // RFC822 message\n    \n    // SES transport:\n    sesMessageId: string,          // AWS SES Message ID\n    \n    // JSON transport:\n    message: object | string       // Normalized message data\n}\n```\n\n### Usage\n\n```javascript\nconst info = await transporter.sendMail({...});\nconsole.log(info.messageId);     // '<abc123@example.com>'\nconsole.log(info.envelope.from); // 'sender@example.com'\nconsole.log(info.envelope.to);   // ['recipient@example.com']\n```\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Nodemailer Thread Headers\n\nSource: https://github.com/nodemailer/nodemailer/blob/master/_autodocs/quick-reference.md\n\nConfigure email threading by setting 'messageId', 'references', and 'inReplyTo' headers. This helps group related emails in clients that support threading.\n\n```javascript\n{\n    messageId: '<custom-id@example.com>',\n    references: '<msg1@example.com> <msg2@example.com>',\n    inReplyTo: '<msg2@example.com>'\n}\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Handle Nodemailer Authentication Errors\n\nSource: https://github.com/nodemailer/nodemailer/blob/master/_autodocs/authentication.md\n\nUse a try-catch block to gracefully handle potential errors during email sending. Specifically check for 'EAUTH' (general authentication failure) and 'EOAUTH2' (OAuth2 token issues) error codes to provide targeted feedback.\n\n```javascript\nconst errors = require('nodemailer/lib/errors');\n\ntry {\n    await transporter.sendMail({...});\n} catch (err) {\n    if (err.code === errors.EAUTH) {\n        console.error('Authentication failed');\n        console.error('Check credentials');\n    } else if (err.code === errors.EOAUTH2) {\n        console.error('OAuth2 token error');\n        console.error('Refresh token may be invalid or expired');\n    }\n}\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Catching ESENDMAIL Errors with Sendmail Transport\n\nSource: https://github.com/nodemailer/nodemailer/blob/master/_autodocs/errors.md\n\nUse this snippet to catch errors related to the Sendmail command. Ensure the sendmail binary is accessible and configured correctly.\n\n```javascript\ntry {\n    const transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({\n        sendmail: true,\n        path: '/usr/sbin/sendmail'\n    });\n    await transporter.sendMail({\n        from: 'sender@example.com',\n        to: 'recipient@example.com',\n        subject: 'Test',\n        text: 'Hello'\n    });\n} catch (err) {\n    if (err.code === 'ESENDMAIL') {\n        console.error('Sendmail error:', err.message);\n    }\n}\n```"}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_36f90d33-711e-4f7f-9ab4-cbe6155a10e","startedAtMs":"1782957219535","completedAtMs":"1782957225484"},"model_call_id":"7e5022f7-c767-4b04-a8e4-816de5d91a39-3-9yhn","session_id":"96149331-134f-48b3-9ea0-fe7607af1532","timestamp_ms":1782957225468}
{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_57bc3c38-d454-487a-89ed-ea9328df875","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs","query":"pgEnum jsonb default partial index unique constraint foreign key cascade drizzle schema"},"toolCallId":"tool_57bc3c38-d454-487a-89ed-ea9328df875","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Declare a Simple Foreign Key in Drizzle ORM and SQL\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/pg/indexes-constraints.mdx\n\nDeclare a foreign key constraint on a single column, linking a child table to a parent table's primary key. This prevents actions that would break referential integrity.\n\n```typescript\nimport { serial, text, integer, pgTable } from \"drizzle-orm/pg-core\";\n\nexport const user = pgTable(\"user\", {\n\tid: serial(\"id\"),\n\tname: text(\"name\")\n});\n\nexport const book = pgTable(\"book\", {\n\tid: serial(\"id\"),\n\tname: text(\"name\"),\n\tauthorId: integer(\"author_id\").references(() => user.id)\n});\n```\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE \"user\" (\n\t\"id\" serial,\n\t\"name\" text\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE \"book\" (\n\t\"id\" serial,\n\t\"name\" text,\n\t\"author_id\" integer\n);\n\nALTER TABLE \"book\" ADD CONSTRAINT \"book_author_id_user_id_fkey\" FOREIGN KEY (\"author_id\") REFERENCES \"user\"(\"id\");\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Define MSSQL Schema with Drizzle ORM\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/mssql/seed-overview.mdx\n\nThis snippet defines a comprehensive MSSQL database schema using Drizzle ORM, including multiple tables with various column types, primary keys, identity columns, and foreign key constraints with `onDelete: 'cascade'`.\n\n```ts\nimport type { AnyColumn } from \"drizzle-orm\";\nimport { int, numeric, mssqlTable, text, datetime2, varchar } from \"drizzle-orm/mssql-core\";\n\nexport const customers = mssqlTable('customer', {\n\tid: varchar({ length: 256 }).primaryKey(),\n\tcompanyName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactTitle: text().notNull(),\n\taddress: text().notNull(),\n\tcity: text().notNull(),\n\tpostalCode: text(),\n\tregion: text(),\n\tcountry: text().notNull(),\n\tphone: text().notNull(),\n\tfax: text(),\n});\n\nexport const employees = mssqlTable(\n\t'employee',\n\t{\n\t\tid: int().primaryKey().identity(),\n\t\tlastName: text().notNull(),\n\t\tfirstName: text(),\n\t\ttitle: text().notNull(),\n\t\ttitleOfCourtesy: text().notNull(),\n\t\tbirthDate: datetime2().notNull(),\n\t\thireDate: datetime2().notNull(),\n\t\taddress: text().notNull(),\n\t\tcity: text().notNull(),\n\t\tpostalCode: text().notNull(),\n\t\tcountry: text().notNull(),\n\t\thomePhone: text().notNull(),\n\t\textension: int().notNull(),\n\t\tnotes: text().notNull(),\n\t\treportsTo: int().references((): AnyColumn => employees.id),\n\t\tphotoPath: text(),\n\t},\n);\n\nexport const orders = mssqlTable('order', {\n\tid: int().primaryKey().identity(),\n\torderDate: datetime2().notNull(),\n\trequiredDate: datetime2().notNull(),\n\tshippedDate: datetime2(),\n\tshipVia: int().notNull(),\n\tfreight: numeric().notNull(),\n\tshipName: text().notNull(),\n\tshipCity: text().notNull(),\n\tshipRegion: text(),\n\tshipPostalCode: text(),\n\tshipCountry: text().notNull(),\n\n\tcustomerId: text().notNull().references(() => customers.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n\n\temployeeId: int().notNull().references(() => employees.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n});\n\nexport const suppliers = mssqlTable('supplier', {\n\tid: int().primaryKey().identity(),\n\tcompanyName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactTitle: text().notNull(),\n\taddress: text().notNull(),\n\tcity: text().notNull(),\n\tregion: text(),\n\tpostalCode: text().notNull(),\n\tcountry: text().notNull(),\n\tphone: text().notNull(),\n});\n\nexport const products = mssqlTable('product', {\n\tid: int().primaryKey().identity(),\n\tname: varchar({ length: 255 }).notNull(),\n\tquantityPerUnit: text().notNull(),\n\tunitPrice: numeric().notNull(),\n\tunitsInStock: int().notNull(),\n\tunitsOnOrder: int().notNull(),\n\treorderLevel: int().notNull(),\n\tdiscontinued: int().notNull(),\n\n\tsupplierId: int().notNull().references(() => suppliers.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n});\n\nexport const details = mssqlTable('order_detail', {\n\tunitPrice: numeric().notNull(),\n\tquantity: int().notNull(),\n\tdiscount: numeric().notNull(),\n\n\torderId: int().notNull().references(() => orders.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n\n\tproductId: int().notNull().references(() => products.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' })\n});\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Define Complex MySQL Schema with Drizzle ORM\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/mysql/seed-overview.mdx\n\nUse this snippet to define a multi-table MySQL schema with Drizzle ORM, including primary keys, auto-incrementing integers, various data types (varchar, text, int, timestamp, numeric), and foreign key constraints with 'onDelete: 'cascade''.\n\n```ts\nimport type { AnyColumn } from \"drizzle-orm\";\nimport { int, numeric, mysqlTable, text, timestamp, varchar } from \"drizzle-orm/mysql-core\";\n\nexport const customers = mysqlTable('customer', {\n\tid: varchar({ length: 256 }).primaryKey(),\n\tcompanyName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactTitle: text().notNull(),\n\taddress: text().notNull(),\n\tcity: text().notNull(),\n\tpostalCode: text(),\n\tregion: text(),\n\tcountry: text().notNull(),\n\tphone: text().notNull(),\n\tfax: text(),\n});\n\nexport const employees = mysqlTable(\n\t'employee',\n\t{\n\t\tid: int().primaryKey().autoincrement(),\n\t\tlastName: text().notNull(),\n\t\tfirstName: text(),\n\t\ttitle: text().notNull(),\n\t\ttitleOfCourtesy: text().notNull(),\n\t\tbirthDate: timestamp().notNull(),\n\t\thireDate: timestamp().notNull(),\n\t\taddress: text().notNull(),\n\t\tcity: text().notNull(),\n\t\tpostalCode: text().notNull(),\n\t\tcountry: text().notNull(),\n\t\thomePhone: text().notNull(),\n\t\textension: int().notNull(),\n\t\tnotes: text().notNull(),\n\t\treportsTo: int().references((): AnyColumn => employees.id),\n\t\tphotoPath: text(),\n\t},\n);\n\nexport const orders = mysqlTable('order', {\n\tid: int().primaryKey().autoincrement(),\n\torderDate: timestamp().notNull(),\n\trequiredDate: timestamp().notNull(),\n\tshippedDate: timestamp(),\n\tshipVia: int().notNull(),\n\tfreight: numeric().notNull(),\n\tshipName: text().notNull(),\n\tshipCity: text().notNull(),\n\tshipRegion: text(),\n\tshipPostalCode: text(),\n\tshipCountry: text().notNull(),\n\n\tcustomerId: text().notNull().references(() => customers.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n\n\temployeeId: int().notNull().references(() => employees.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n});\n\nexport const suppliers = mysqlTable('supplier', {\n\tid: int().primaryKey().autoincrement(),\n\tcompanyName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactName: text().notNull(),\n\tcontactTitle: text().notNull(),\n\taddress: text().notNull(),\n\tcity: text().notNull(),\n\tregion: text(),\n\tpostalCode: text().notNull(),\n\tcountry: text().notNull(),\n\tphone: text().notNull(),\n});\n\nexport const products = mysqlTable('product', {\n\tid: int().primaryKey().autoincrement(),\n\tname: varchar({ length: 255 }).notNull(),\n\tquantityPerUnit: text().notNull(),\n\tunitPrice: numeric().notNull(),\n\tunitsInStock: int().notNull(),\n\tunitsOnOrder: int().notNull(),\n\treorderLevel: int().notNull(),\n\tdiscontinued: int().notNull(),\n\n\tsupplierId: int().notNull().references(() => suppliers.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n});\n\nexport const details = mysqlTable('order_detail', {\n\tunitPrice: numeric().notNull(),\n\tquantity: int().notNull(),\n\tdiscount: numeric().notNull(),\n\n\torderId: int().notNull().references(() => orders.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n\n\tproductId: int().notNull().references(() => products.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }),\n});\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Define JSONB Columns with Drizzle ORM\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/pg/column-types.mdx\n\nUse `jsonb()` to define JSONB columns in a Drizzle ORM table schema, including options for default values using plain objects or SQL expressions.\n\n```typescript\nimport { jsonb, pgTable } from \"drizzle-orm/pg-core\";\n\nexport const table = pgTable('table', {\n\tjsonb1: jsonb(),\n\tjsonb2: jsonb().default({ foo: \"bar\" }),\n\tjsonb3: jsonb().default(sql`'{\"foo\": \"bar\"}'`),\n});\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Declare Standard and Unique Indexes in Drizzle ORM and SQL\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/pg/indexes-constraints.mdx\n\nCreate both standard and unique indexes on table columns to improve query performance and enforce uniqueness constraints.\n\n```typescript\nimport { serial, text, index, uniqueIndex, pgTable } from \"drizzle-orm/pg-core\";\n\nexport const user = pgTable(\"user\", {\n  id: serial().primaryKey(),\n  name: text(),\n  email: text()\n}, (table) => [\n  index(\"name_idx\").on(table.name),\n  uniqueIndex(\"email_idx\").on(table.email)\n]);\n```\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE \"user\" (\n\t...\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX \"name_idx\" ON \"user\" (\"name\");\nCREATE UNIQUE INDEX \"email_idx\" ON \"user\" (\"email\");\n```"}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_57bc3c38-d454-487a-89ed-ea9328df875","startedAtMs":"1782957219911","completedAtMs":"1782957226951"},"model_call_id":"7e5022f7-c767-4b04-a8e4-816de5d91a39-3-9yhn","session_id":"96149331-134f-48b3-9ea0-fe7607af1532","timestamp_ms":1782957226925}
