{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_bbd516e0-27df-4f31-be28-f25290badd8","tool_call":{"grepToolCall":{"args":{"pattern":"Phase 4|mailbox|message","path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-4-mail/docs/implementations/phases/Quiksend-Implementation-Plan-Phases-2-10.md","contextAfter":3,"caseInsensitive":false,"multiline":false,"toolCallId":"tool_bbd516e0-27df-4f31-be28-f25290badd8","offset":0},"result":{"success":{"pattern":"Phase 4|mailbox|message","path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-4-mail/docs/implementations/phases/Quiksend-Implementation-Plan-Phases-2-10.md","outputMode":"content","workspaceResults":{"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-4-mail":{"content":{"matches":[{"file":"docs/implementations/phases/Quiksend-Implementation-Plan-Phases-2-10.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":54,"content":"  connecting CRMs/mailboxes, managing billing, and deleting workspaces are admin-only;","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":55,"content":"  day-to-day prospect/sequence work is any member.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":56,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":57,"content":"### Migrations","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":69,"content":"Job names are namespaced: `sequence.tick`, `sequence.step`, `mailbox.poll`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":70,"content":"`crm.sync`, `crm.writeback`, `webhook.deliver`, `ai.research`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":71,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":72,"content":"> **Sequencing note (important):** the ticket outline introduces pg-boss in Phase 6, but","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":73,"content":"> Phase 3 (CRM webhooks/sync) and Phase 4 (send) both benefit from async processing.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":74,"content":"> **Recommended adjustment:** stand up the pg-boss bootstrap (a slim version of R-061 —","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":75,"content":"> connection, schema install, a `worker` process that registers handlers) in **Phase 3**,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":76,"content":"> and keep only the _scheduler tick_ and _step executor_ in Phase 6. Phases below are","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":78,"content":"> handler and Phase 4's send can run inline (synchronously in the server fn) as an","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":79,"content":"> interim, with a note to move them onto the queue when it lands.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":80,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":81,"content":"### Testing & Definition of Done","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":102,"content":"- `packages/mail` (Phase 4) — `MailboxAdapter` interface + Gmail/Graph/SMTP","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":103,"content":"  implementations, react-email rendering, MIME + threading/compliance headers.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":104,"content":"- `packages/core` (Phase 6) — the enrollment state machine and pure transition/schedule","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":105,"content":"  functions (no I/O; the most heavily unit-tested package).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":115,"content":"| 4     | `mailbox`, `message` (the outbound/anchor store; inbound added in P7)                                               |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":116,"content":"| 5     | `sequence`, `sequence_step`, `enrollment`                                                                           |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":117,"content":"| 6     | `task`, `send_reservation` (or a counter), `job_log`; extends `enrollment` (anchor, attempt, error)                 |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":118,"content":"| 7     | `suppression`; extends `message` (inbound direction, bounce metadata), thread linkage                               |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":119,"content":"| 8     | `research_profile` (+ pgvector embedding), `value_prop`, `generation`                                               |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":120,"content":"| 9     | `crm_writeback_log`; analytics rollup views/tables                                                                  |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":121,"content":"| 10    | `api_usage`, `webhook_endpoint`, `webhook_delivery`, `unsubscribe_token`                                            |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":167,"content":"  renders create/import/field-change events and shows empty \"sequence history / messages\"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":168,"content":"  sections that Phases 5–7 populate.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":169,"content":"- CSV import wizard: upload → parse headers → **column-mapping step** (map each CSV","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":170,"content":"  column to a prospect/company field or \"ignore\", remember mappings per org) → preview +","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":303,"content":"## Phase 4 — Mailboxes & single send","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":304,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":305,"content":"**Goal.** Connect sending identities (Gmail, Microsoft, SMTP), send a real one-off email","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":306,"content":"through them, and record it — capturing the threading anchor and writing the `message`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":307,"content":"row that the engine (Phase 6) and inbox (Phase 7) build on. Plus deliverability health","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":308,"content":"(SPF/DKIM/DMARC).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":309,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":326,"content":"  `threadId` for replies). Capture the returned message/thread ids and the RFC","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":327,"content":"  `Message-ID`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":328,"content":"- **Microsoft** — via Nango-managed OAuth; send via Microsoft Graph. Capture","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":329,"content":"  Graph/internet message ids for threading.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":330,"content":"- **SMTP** — nodemailer; store SMTP creds encrypted at rest. Threading via","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":331,"content":"  `In-Reply-To`/`References` headers you set yourself.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":332,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":335,"content":"- **`mailbox`** — `id`, `organization_id`, `owner_user_id`, `provider`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":336,"content":"  (`gmail`/`microsoft`/`smtp`), `address`, `display_name`/`from_name`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":337,"content":"  `nango_connection_id` (nullable), `smtp_config jsonb` (nullable, encrypted),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":338,"content":"  `daily_cap`, `send_window` (start/end + `tz`), `throttle_seconds`, `signature_html`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":340,"content":"- **`message`** — the anchor + audit store. `id`, `organization_id`, `mailbox_id`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":341,"content":"  `prospect_id`, `enrollment_id` (nullable, set by the engine), `direction`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":342,"content":"  (`outbound` now; `inbound` in P7), `subject`, `body_html`/`body_text`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":343,"content":"  `message_id_header` (RFC Message-ID — the **anchor**), `provider_message_id`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":344,"content":"  `provider_thread_id`, `in_reply_to`, `references`, `status`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":345,"content":"  (`sent`/`failed`/`bounced`/`received`), `sent_at`, timestamps. Index the header ids for","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":346,"content":"  thread matching in P7.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":356,"content":"  (RFC `Message-ID` + provider `threadId`) → write the outbound `message`. This anchor","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":357,"content":"  is exactly what the manual-first engine threads follow-ups under.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":358,"content":"- **Health:** SPF/DKIM/DMARC checked via DNS lookups for the sending domain; surface","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":359,"content":"  flags on the mailbox and warn on send from an unauthenticated domain.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":360,"content":"- **Caps/window/throttle** are _defined_ here (mailbox fields) and _enforced_ by","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":361,"content":"  `reserveSendSlot` in Phase 6; a single manual send should still respect a basic guard.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":362,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":363,"content":"### Tickets","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":366,"content":"- **R-041** — mailbox connect UI + settings (cap/window/throttle/signature/from-name).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":367,"content":"- **R-042** — react-email + MIME builder + threading headers + unsubscribe/address footer.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":368,"content":"- **R-043** — compose & send one-off; capture anchor; write outbound `message`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":369,"content":"- **R-044** — SPF/DKIM/DMARC checker + health flags.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":370,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":371,"content":"### Testing","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":383,"content":"\"send-as\"/identity constraints; bounce handling deferred to P7 but design `message`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":384,"content":"to record it.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":385,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":386,"content":"### Exit (AC B1–B3, E1)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":388,"content":"Connect a mailbox, send a manual email, and see it correctly threaded at the provider and","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":389,"content":"recorded as a `message` with its anchor.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":390,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":391,"content":"---","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":392,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":396,"content":"prospects (single + bulk) with mailbox round-robin and an accurate schedule preview.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":397,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":398,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 2 (prospects/lists), Phase 4 (mailboxes; templates that will send).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":399,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":400,"content":"### Data model","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":401,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":404,"content":"  `mailbox_ids[]`, `stop_on_reply`), `deleted_at`, timestamps.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":405,"content":"- **`sequence_step`** — `id`, `organization_id`, `sequence_id`, `index` (order),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":406,"content":"  `type` (`manual_email`/`auto_email`/`wait`/`task`), `delay` (interval — time after the","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":407,"content":"  previous step), `config jsonb` (subject/body template, task instructions, wait","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":411,"content":"  `sequence_id`, `prospect_id`, `mailbox_id` (round-robin assigned), `state` (the P6 state","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":412,"content":"  machine), `current_step_index`, `next_run_at`, `anchor_message_id` (nullable),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":413,"content":"  `ab_bucket`, timestamps. Unique `(organization_id, sequence_id, prospect_id)` — prevent","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":414,"content":"  double-enrollment.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":415,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":421,"content":"throttle/mailboxes/stop-on-reply). Enroll dialog: pick prospects or a list → preview the","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":422,"content":"computed schedule → confirm.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":423,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":424,"content":"### Mechanics","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":429,"content":"- **Enrollment + round-robin:** bulk enroll assigns mailboxes round-robin across the","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":430,"content":"  sequence's `mailbox_ids` to spread volume. Enforce the unique constraint to make","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":431,"content":"  re-enrolling a no-op (or an explicit \"re-enroll\" action).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":432,"content":"- **Schedule preview** computes per-step times from `delay` + send window + throttle —","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":433,"content":"  and **must use the same function the engine uses** (extract it into `packages/core` in","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":442,"content":"- **R-052** — sequence settings (window/tz/throttle/mailboxes/stop-on-reply).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":443,"content":"- **R-053** — enrollment creation (single + bulk) with mailbox round-robin + schedule","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":444,"content":"  preview.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":445,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":446,"content":"### Testing","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":450,"content":"mailbox spread, no duplicates; draft→active transitions.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":451,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":452,"content":"### Risks & decisions","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":453,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":474,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 5 (sequence/step/enrollment), Phase 4 (adapters + `message` anchor),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":475,"content":"Phase 3 (pg-boss).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":476,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":477,"content":"### New package: `packages/core` (pure, no I/O)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":494,"content":"`sendAuto(step)`, `captureAnchor(message)`, `terminate(reason)`, `emitEvent(...)`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":495,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":496,"content":"### Scheduler & executor (in `apps/worker`)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":497,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":508,"content":"    threaded under `anchor_message_id` → write `message` → `advance`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":509,"content":"- **`reserveSendSlot(mailbox)`** enforces `daily_cap`, `send_window` (in the mailbox tz),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":510,"content":"  and `throttle_seconds`. Make the reservation atomic (a `send_reservation` row or an","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":511,"content":"  atomic counter within the current window, taken under lock) so concurrent workers can't","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":512,"content":"  both send past the cap. If no slot, reschedule to the next open window.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":518,"content":"2. User edits and sends from their own mailbox (Phase 4 send path).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":519,"content":"3. On send, the RFC `Message-ID` + `threadId` become the enrollment's **anchor**.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":520,"content":"4. Subsequent `auto_email` follow-ups are sent as replies with `In-Reply-To`/`References`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":521,"content":"   set to the anchor, so they land in the same thread the human started.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":523,"content":"   already-sent message as the anchor, beginning automated follow-ups on a real","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":524,"content":"   human-sent thread.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":525,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":526,"content":"### Data model","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":530,"content":"- **`send_reservation`** (or a windowed counter) — mailbox slot accounting for","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":531,"content":"  cap/window/throttle.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":532,"content":"- Extend **`enrollment`**: `anchor_message_id`, `attempt_count`, `last_error`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":533,"content":"  `idempotency_key` per (enrollment, step, attempt).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":534,"content":"- **`job_log`** — dead-letter + retry audit (or lean on pg-boss's own tables + Sentry).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":535,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":542,"content":"- **Exactly-once-ish send:** the reservation + idempotency key + writing `message` before","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":543,"content":"  ack together make a re-run safe (check \"did we already send this step?\" before sending).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":544,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":545,"content":"### Tickets","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":583,"content":"**Goal.** Close the loop: detect replies and bounces on the mailboxes, feed them to the","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":584,"content":"engine (stop-on-reply, suppress-on-bounce), and give users a unified inbox to read and","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":585,"content":"respond.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":586,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":587,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 6 (engine transitions), Phase 4 (`message` anchor store + adapters).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":588,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":589,"content":"### Data model","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":590,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":594,"content":"- **Extend `message`** for inbound: `direction = inbound`, `bounce_type`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":595,"content":"  (`hard`/`soft`/none), `dsn jsonb`, `in_reply_to`/`references` for matching, and a","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":596,"content":"  `thread_id`/link back to the enrollment.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":597,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":600,"content":"- **Inbound poller (worker job `mailbox.poll`):** per mailbox, poll for new inbound mail —","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":601,"content":"  Gmail (history/messages since a stored cursor), Microsoft Graph (delta queries), IMAP","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":602,"content":"  (for SMTP mailboxes). Store a per-mailbox cursor; dedupe by provider message id.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":603,"content":"- **Thread matching:** match inbound `In-Reply-To`/`References` against the","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":604,"content":"  `message_id_header` anchors (indexed in P4) to find the enrollment/prospect. Normalize","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":605,"content":"  Message-IDs across providers (angle brackets, casing).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":606,"content":"- **Bounce/DSN parsing:** detect delivery-status notifications (multipart/report,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":607,"content":"  RFC 3464 status codes, provider-specific bounce formats). Classify hard vs. soft.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":616,"content":"Unified inbox: list with filters (unread, replied, bounced, by sequence/mailbox), thread","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":617,"content":"view (the full outbound+inbound conversation via the anchor), reply composer (sends","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":618,"content":"through the same Phase 4 path, threaded), and a sentiment/triage tag (simple heuristic","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":619,"content":"now; AI-assisted in Phase 8).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":620,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":621,"content":"### Tickets","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":726,"content":"comparison, per-mailbox volume/bounce.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":727,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":728,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 3 (Nango connections + mapping), Phase 6/7 (send/reply events).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":729,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":733,"content":"  (`send`/`reply`/`status`), `entity` (prospect/message), `external_ref`, `status`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":734,"content":"  `idempotency_key`, timestamps. Prevents double-logging on retry.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":735,"content":"- **Analytics** — start with SQL aggregate **views** over `enrollment`/`message`/","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":736,"content":"  `sequence_step`; if they get slow, add periodically-refreshed **rollup tables**","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":737,"content":"  (`sequence_stats`, `step_stats`, `mailbox_stats`) updated by a `analytics.rollup` job.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":738,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":739,"content":"### Mechanics","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":740,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":748,"content":"  with basic significance framing), per-mailbox volume + bounce rate (a deliverability","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":749,"content":"  early-warning). Dashboards in `apps/web` (charts via the stack's charting lib).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":750,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":751,"content":"### Tickets","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":755,"content":"- **R-092** — analytics: per-sequence funnel, per-step rates, A/B compare, per-mailbox","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":756,"content":"  volume/bounce.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":757,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":758,"content":"### Testing","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":786,"content":"Phase 4 (compliance footer/headers), Phase 7 (suppression).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":787,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":788,"content":"### Data model","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":789,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":807,"content":"- **Unsubscribe end-to-end:** the `List-Unsubscribe` header + footer link (from Phase 4)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":808,"content":"  resolve to a handler that validates the `unsubscribe_token`, writes a `suppression`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":809,"content":"  and triggers CRM status write-back (Phase 9). Compliant footers (physical address +","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":810,"content":"  clear opt-out) enforced on all sends.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":854,"content":"   Phase 3's webhook/sync processing and Phase 4's send both want async work; standing the","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":855,"content":"   queue up once, early, avoids interim inline hacks. (Phases above assume this.)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":856,"content":"2. **Extract the schedule/window/throttle math into `packages/core` when Phase 6 lands,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":857,"content":"   and have Phase 5's schedule preview import it** — one function, so preview never drifts","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":859,"content":"3. **Design `message` (Phase 4) for inbound from day one** (nullable bounce/DSN/thread","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":860,"content":"   fields) so Phase 7 extends rather than migrates it heavily.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":861,"content":"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true},{"lineNumber":862,"content":"## Appendix B — Cross-cutting risk register","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":true}]}],"totalLines":244,"totalMatchedLines":62,"clientTruncated":false,"ripgrepTruncated":false}}}}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_bbd516e0-27df-4f31-be28-f25290badd8","startedAtMs":"1782957242988","completedAtMs":"1782957246275"},"model_call_id":"7e5022f7-c767-4b04-a8e4-816de5d91a39-4-w07e","session_id":"96149331-134f-48b3-9ea0-fe7607af1532","timestamp_ms":1782957246248}
