{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_f10c88ff-a2ab-4a62-bbae-a2f3dc8f6e9","tool_call":{"readToolCall":{"args":{"path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-4-mail/packages/config/src/env.ts"},"result":{"success":{"content":"import { EnvSchema } from \"./env.schema.ts\";\nimport type { Env } from \"./env.schema.ts\";\n\n/**\n * Eager, fail-fast environment loader. If required vars are missing or malformed the\n * process exits at startup rather than blowing up somewhere deep in a request.\n *\n * The schema itself lives in `env.schema.ts` (no side effects) so it can be imported\n * and unit-tested without triggering this load.\n */\nfunction loadEnv(): Env {\n  const parsed = EnvSchema.safeParse(process.env);\n  if (!parsed.success) {\n    const issues = parsed.error.issues\n      .map((i) => `  - ${i.path.join(\".\") || \"(root)\"}: ${i.message}`)\n      .join(\"\\n\");\n    // Using process.stderr directly so this works before the logger is wired.\n    process.stderr.write(`\\nInvalid environment variables:\\n${issues}\\n\\n`);\n    process.exit(1);\n  }\n  return parsed.data;\n}\n\nexport const env: Env = loadEnv();\nexport { EnvSchema };\nexport type { Env };\n","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalLines":27,"fileSize":917,"path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-4-mail/packages/config/src/env.ts","readRange":{"startLine":1,"endLine":27},"relatedCursorRulePaths":[],"relatedCursorRules":[]}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_f10c88ff-a2ab-4a62-bbae-a2f3dc8f6e9","startedAtMs":"1782957470199","completedAtMs":"1782957472394"},"model_call_id":"7e5022f7-c767-4b04-a8e4-816de5d91a39-13-gr0e","session_id":"96149331-134f-48b3-9ea0-fe7607af1532","timestamp_ms":1782957472421}
{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_dd9c6e80-e597-4c9f-a363-ebb4e0e8b25","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/websites/tanstack_start","query":"createServerFn validator input middleware handler POST"},"toolCallId":"tool_dd9c6e80-e597-4c9f-a363-ebb4e0e8b25","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Define a Server Function with Basic Parameters and Validation (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/server-functions.md\n\nUse \"createServerFn\" with a simple validator function to define a server function that accepts basic typed parameters and returns a greeting.\n\n```tsx\nimport { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'\n\nexport const greetUser = createServerFn({ method: 'GET' })\n  .validator((data: { name: string }) => data)\n  .handler(async ({ data }) => {\n    return `Hello, ${data.name}!`\n  })\n\nawait greetUser({ data: { name: 'John' } })\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### createServerFn()\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/execution-model.md\n\nCreates a function that executes on the server but can be called from the client, enabling RPC calls and data mutations.\n\n```APIDOC\n## createServerFn()\n\n### Description\nCreates a function that executes exclusively on the server but can be invoked from client-side code. This is ideal for Remote Procedure Calls (RPC) and data mutations that require server-side logic or access to server-only resources.\n\n### Usage\n```tsx\nimport { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'\n\nconst updateUser = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' })\n  .validator((data: UserData) => data)\n  .handler(async ({ data }) => {\n    // This code only runs on the server\n    return await db.users.update(data)\n  })\n// updateUser can now be called from client-side code\n```\n\n### Parameters\n- **options** (object) - Required - Configuration options for the server function.\n    - **method** (string) - Required - The HTTP method to use for the RPC call (e.g., 'POST').\n\n### Returns\n(function) - A callable function that, when invoked from the client, triggers the server-side handler.\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Define a Server Function in TanStack Start\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/start-vs-nextjs.md\n\nThis snippet demonstrates defining a server-side function in TanStack Start with built-in input validation using Zod, middleware support, and full type inference.\n\n```tsx\nexport const createPost = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' })\n  .validator(z.object({ title: z.string().min(1) }))\n  .middleware([authMiddleware])\n  .handler(async ({ data, context }) => {\n    // data is typed and validated\n    // context comes from middleware, also typed\n    return db.posts.create({ title: data.title })\n  })\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Validate User Input with Zod in TypeScript\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/authentication.md\n\nIllustrates how to use Zod for robust input validation on a server function. Defines a schema for email and password, ensuring data integrity before processing.\n\n```tsx\nimport { z } from 'zod'\n\nconst loginSchema = z.object({\n  email: z.string().email().max(255),\n  password: z.string().min(8).max(100)\n})\n\nexport const loginFn = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' })\n  .validator((data) => loginSchema.parse(data))\n  .handler(async ({ data }) => {\n    // data is now validated\n  })\n\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Define Server Functions with createServerFn in TypeScript\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/server-functions.md\n\nUse `createServerFn()` to define server-side logic, specifying the HTTP method (GET by default, or POST explicitly). These functions encapsulate server-only operations.\n\n```tsx\nimport { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'\n\n// GET request (default)\nexport const getData = createServerFn().handler(async () => {\n  return { message: 'Hello from server!' }\n})\n\n// POST request\nexport const saveData = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' }).handler(async () => {\n  // Server-only logic\n  return { success: true }\n})\n```"}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_dd9c6e80-e597-4c9f-a363-ebb4e0e8b25","startedAtMs":"1782957469530","completedAtMs":"1782957474887"},"model_call_id":"7e5022f7-c767-4b04-a8e4-816de5d91a39-13-gr0e","session_id":"96149331-134f-48b3-9ea0-fe7607af1532","timestamp_ms":1782957474907}
